=====Usage notes=====
* {{lang|ja|だ}} is the only commonly used modern Japanese verb with the terminal form ({{ja-l|終止形}}) distinct from the attributive form ({{ja-l|連体形}}). As relative clauses in Japanese are syntactically equivalent to attributives, relative clauses must end in the attributive form. Thus {{lang|ja|だ}}, as a terminal form, cannot appear at the end of a relative clause. The following forms are used instead of {{lang|ja|だ}} in such places:
:* Use {{lang|ja|の}} after nouns, adverbs or prepositional phrases. But use {{lang|ja|な}} before the nominalizer {{ja-l|の}}.
:: {{ja-x|[[学%生]]'''の'''アリス|がく%せい '''の''' ^アリス|Alice, who '''is''' a student}}
:: {{ja-x|ここ[[まで]]'''の'''あらすじ|ここまで '''の''' あらすじ|the plot summary until now}}
:: {{ja-x|後%味も[[すっきり]]'''な'''のが特%徴です。|あと%あじ も すっきり '''な''' の が とく%ちょう です。|That the aftertaste '''is''' refreshing too is its distinguishing feature.}}
:: {{ja-x|今日は[[休み]]'''な'''ので早%起きしてなかった。|きょう は やすみ '''な''' の で はや%おき して なかった。|I didn't get up early because it '''is''' a holiday today.}}
:* Use {{lang|ja|な}} after a na-adjective.
:: {{ja-x|実%家が[[裕%福]]'''な'''友人|じっ%か が ゆう%ふく '''な''' ゆうじん|a friend whose family '''is''' rich}}
:* Alternatively, {{lang|ja|である}} can be used when following nouns and denoting the meaning "to be".
:: {{ja-x|[[学%生]]'''である'''アリス|がく%せい '''である''' ^アリス|Alice, who '''is''' a student}}
* This word is phonologically an [[enclitic]], similar to [[particle]]s. It is classified as {{m|ja|助動詞|tr=jodōshi||auxiliary verb}} in traditional Japanese grammar.

